    "creation_date" : 1659010629,
    "answer_id" : 73152774,
    "question_id" : 2156120,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Just use MicroStream Object Copier.</p>\n<pre><code>ObjectCopier objectCopier = ObjectCopier.New();\nCustomer customer = root.getCustomer(id);\nCustomer customerCopy = objectCopier.copy(customer);\n</code></pre>\n<p>This utility provides the full deep copy of any object graph in Java. Be careful of the cyclic references. You can easily make o copy of your whole memory graph.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.microstream.one/manual/storage/storing-data/deep-copy.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://docs.microstream.one/manual/storage/storing-data/deep-copy.html</a></p>\n"
  }, {
